# Angular reference (entire application)

The **complete** legacy Angular app is linked read-only under:

- `external-src/angular/` (preferred)
- `external-src/goldcollegeerp_2024_dev3/` (same tree)

## Layout

| Area | Path |
|---|---|
| All feature modules (~129) | `external-src/angular/src/app/main/apps/` |
| Shared UI / constants | `external-src/angular/src/app/main/common/` |
| Models | `external-src/angular/src/app/main/models/` |
| Services | `external-src/angular/src/app/main/services/` |
| Pages | `external-src/angular/src/app/main/pages/` |

Only **scholarship** is migrated in Next.js (`src/app/(pages)/(protected)/scholarship-management/`). For any other feature, read the matching folder under `external-src/angular/src/app/main/apps/<feature>/` before implementing.

Do not import Angular code into Next.js. Use the reference for templates, fields, API calls, and business rules only.
